{"id": 7145, "title": "Ticket #7145: Memory leak in CEDAR SSL authentication", "description": "<blockquote>\nThe code changes to make SSL authentication non-blocking introduced a major memory leak. It calls unique_ptr::release() expecting it to free the relevant object. But release() doesn't do that. The code should call unique_ptr::reset() instead.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Aug-07 15:28</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=57626\">[57626]</a></span>: Add SSL memory leak as a known issue in 8.9.2. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7145\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7145'); return false;\" title=\"Memory leak in CEDAR SSL authentication\">#7145</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Jul-25 11:01</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=57484\">[57484]</a></span>: Docs for CEDAR SSL memory leak fix. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7145\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7145'); return false;\" title=\"Memory leak in CEDAR SSL authentication\">#7145</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Jul-10 16:27</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=57375\">[57375]</a></span>: Fix big memory leak in CEDAR SSL authentication. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7145\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7145'); return false;\" title=\"Memory leak in CEDAR SSL authentication\">#7145</a></span> To free an object managed by unique_ptr, you have to call reset(), not release().  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2019-Jul-25 11:01", "status": "resolved", "created": "2019-Jul-10 15:13", "fixed_version": "2019-Jul-10 15:13", "broken_version": "v080902", "priority": "1", "subsystem": "Security", "assigned_to": "jfrey", "derived_from": "#6981", "creator": "jfrey", "rust": "", "customer_group": "chtc", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}